{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "4f053750-b033-4d14-83c2-1cb6b29b5378",
    "name": "Ticketing Microservices",
    "description": "Ticketing microservices collection aligned with the controllers in this project.\n\nBASE\n\n- Base URL: {{baseUrl}}\n- Default gateway URL: http://localhost:8080\n\nHOW IDs ARE STORED (IMPORTANT)\n\n- This collection stores IDs in COLLECTION variables (pm.collectionVariables)\n- customerId, eventId, ticketInventoryId, ticketOrderId\n- This works even if you do NOT select a Postman Environment.\n\nSUGGESTED RUN ORDER\n\n1) Customers -> Create Customer\n2) Events -> Create Event\n3) Events -> Activate Event\n4) Ticket Inventories -> Create Ticket Inventory\n5) Ticket Orders -> Create Ticket Order\n\nENDPOINT LIST (DOCUMENTATION)\n\nCUSTOMERS\n- POST /api/customers\n- GET /api/customers\n- GET /api/customers/{id}\n- PUT /api/customers/{id}\n- DELETE /api/customers/{id}\n- GET /api/customers/{id}/eligibility\n\nEVENTS\n- POST /api/events\n- GET /api/events\n- GET /api/events/{id}\n- PUT /api/events/{id}\n- POST /api/events/{id}/activate\n- POST /api/events/{id}/cancel\n- GET /api/events/{id}/eligibility\n- DELETE /api/events/{id}\n\nTICKET INVENTORIES\n- POST /api/ticket-inventories\n- GET /api/ticket-inventories\n- GET /api/ticket-inventories/{id}\n- PUT /api/ticket-inventories/{id}\n- DELETE /api/ticket-inventories/{id}\n- GET /api/ticket-inventories/eligibility?eventId=...&ticketType=...&quantity=...\n\nTICKET ORDERS\n- POST /api/ticket-orders\n- GET /api/ticket-orders\n- GET /api/ticket-orders/{id}\n- PUT /api/ticket-orders/{id}\n- DELETE /api/ticket-orders/{id}\n\nNOTES\n\n- Requests are routed through Spring Cloud Gateway.\n- Safe for local H2 runs and Docker runs if the gateway is available on port 8080.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "21908877"
  },
